Developing story (Photo: The Republic)

Phoenix police are investigating after a vehicle crashed into a pole Tuesday evening, killing the driver, according to Phoenix Police Department Sgt. Ann Justus.

Police say the driver was heading north on 31st Avenue and collided with a pole at the corner of Voltaire Avenue, near Thunderbird Road.

Phoenix Fire Department crews attempted to extricate an unidentified man but he died at the scene. There were no other occupants in the vehicle.

Speed appears to be a factor, Justus said.

This is a developing story. Check azcentral.com for updates.

